&nbsp;

The following are the histograms of the simulated 6 sided die and a fair 8 sided die generated using the 6 sided die.

<a href="https://fermibot.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/fair_8_from_fair_6.png"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-4160" src="https://fermibot.wordpress.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/fair_8_from_fair_6.png" alt="" width="788" height="253" /></a>

<hr />

Mathematica Code
<pre>Module[{fairEightTree,
  fairSix := Ceiling[Divide[RandomInteger[{1, 6}], 3]]},
  fairEightTree =
      &lt;|1 -&gt; &lt;|1 -&gt; &lt;|1 -&gt; 1, 2 -&gt; 2|&gt;, 2 -&gt; &lt;|1 -&gt; 3, 2 -&gt; 4|&gt;|&gt;,
        2 -&gt; &lt;|1 -&gt; &lt;|1 -&gt; 5, 2 -&gt; 6|&gt;, 2 -&gt; &lt;|1 -&gt; 7, 2 -&gt; 8|&gt;|&gt;|&gt;;
  Histogram[Table[fairEightTree[fairSix][fairSix][fairSix], 100000]]
]</pre>

<hr />

Python Code
<pre>import random
import math


def binaryFromSix():
    return math.ceil(random.randint(1, 6) / 3)


fairEight = {
    1: {1: {1: 1, 2: 2}, 2: {1: 3, 2: 4}},
    2: {1: {1: 5, 2: 6}, 2: {1: 7, 2: 8}}
}

if __name__ == '__main__':
    for i in range(100):
        print(fairEight[binaryFromSix()][binaryFromSix()][binaryFromSix()], end=' ')</pre>

